&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;The Damage of the Earthquake Happening(1)&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Speculant Hunting&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;Damn, the Magistri wants a report for the situation caused by this earthquake at Chester Island. These guys are never interested in us at other times, but they pretend to worry for us!

So can you hunt Speculants? The inspection is already finished up to the more dangerous places. We'll have to inspect by the front of the way because we can't inspect the spot where Serbetus is. I'll do the inspection, you hunt down the Speculants around!&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;Did the guys get a hint?&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;You did a good job. Writing the report is already completed thanks to you.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ef1yh001a><ef1yh001b><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;The Damage of the Earthquake Occurrence(2)&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Deliver the Damage-Report to Mathew&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;You do not know, but maybe there could arise a very dangerous situation.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;I have a really bad feeling about this.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;What brings you here today?&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ef1yh001b><ef1yh001c><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;A Sinister Premonition&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Retis Hunting&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;Hum&amp;#x2026;. We need to investigate a little more because we didn't record every detail. According to the process, I'll tell you some more later.

Did you see this crack while hunting Speculant? In fact a long time ago, this was the entrance to Droes, that had just been closed by some reason. But it seems the entrance has reopened by this earthquake. Can you check the situation inside?&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;I am so curious to see it.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;The mouse has a jewel on its back? It seems to be Retis. Although this is bothersome, you did a good job.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ef1yh001c><ec1ym651a><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;To Droes Dungeon&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Collect Twelve Parasitic Stones&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt; Did you come for buying some stuff? You haven't decided yet? Think quicker. I am really busy.

Hm...Have you heard about this enormous earthquake at chester island? I heard inhabitants were saying that the entrance to Droes Dungeon reopened. Do you want to go there? Then I have a request for you. I'll generously reward you.

There is a unique crystal inside of Droes Dungeon. Its name is Parasitic Stone. The crystal grows by absorbing nutrition on the skin of monsters. Please, bring me a few. What do you think? Will you do it?&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;Listen to me before you go. The monsters with Parasitic Stones on them are faster than others and display group behavior.  So be careful not to face more than one attack at the same time.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt; Is this Parasitic Stone? You've really brought it to me. I love you for that. Here is the prize I promised. It's enough. You should be satisfied. I'll ask you again if I have another request. &amp;#x2026; Hahahaha&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ec1ym651a><ec1ym652a><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Troublesome Predator&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Retis Hunting&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt; Do you know the entrance to Droes Dungeon at Chester Island was opened by an earthquake?
The Retis living in this dungeon ever since then came out and gnawed woods. So the woods' quantity and quality became poor.

Habitually the Retis come out in the evening. We have big trouble dealing with them. I myself can't do it because I have other tasks. You will go hunting Retis in place of me.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;You can find Retis at Droes Dungeon.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt; You did a good job. The damage is reduced compared to before.
 If we don't prevent Retis' continuous increase, we'll get an enormous problem. We have to eliminate them with full attention and without any rest.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ec1ym652a><ef1yh002a><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;An Unpleasant Mouse&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Retis Hunting&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;You know the entrance to Droes reopened again, do you? It was hard to lock it, and this surely will cause some trouble. But this way outsiders won't be able to get into this island as they want. There are monsters called Retis in Droes. The inspection will be easier, if you reduce them. Go and hunt the Retis.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;I hate the sight of mice because of Retis.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt; I wanted to ask you for their extermination, but that would over do it, wouldn't it?  You did a good job. But can you bring some distance between us? You reek of the Retis' smell.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ef1yh002a><ef1yh002b><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;The stinking Monster&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Auder Hunting&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;It's still reeking around, but you are far away enough. Next is this monster leaving such a stench. They are called Auder and dreadful as they are, we almost suffocated by them in Droes. Go and hunt these monsters. Ah, report to Mathew when you caught them! And don't come to me for the time being. I hate to smell it.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;Hurry, go away. Really the Retis' stench is getting more and more terrible.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Haha. Coco horribly dislikes these guys. You did a good gob.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ef1yh002b><ef1yh003a><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Elimination of an anxiety Element&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Retis Hunting&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;Hey, I heard that there is a bunch of mice in Droes. They don't show up around here, do they? Hum, but I feel uncomfortable. Can you eliminate this bunch of mice? Although they might not appear here, what if the number of these guys increases? What if they come near my precious ship, no!&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;Haha. I'm not letting it concern me if they come around my ship&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Did you come back? This is your prize. Please keep on eliminating them, so that the number of the guys doesn't increase.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ef1yh003a><ef1yh004a><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Request of a Shy Girl&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Conversation with Amalrie&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;Do you have some time? Don't glare at me that way, I don't have any intention of working you too hard. Do you know Amalrie? She is working as Bartender here. She asked for someone to help her. If you have time, go see her!&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;Just wait. Next time I'll make you work hard like a horse.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Ah, you've come here?&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ef1yh004a><ef1yh004b><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Tea Test Material&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Jewel-Flower Collection&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;How are you. Well&amp;#x2026;I'd like to ask you a favor. If you are too busy, you can do it later.

What I'd like to ask of you, is to pick a flower of the back of this monster called Craft in Droes. I've seen some books describing the way of making tea with this flower. Please let me ask you for this favor.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;What does the flower look like?&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Oh, thank you so much. Please wait a minute.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ef1yh004b><ef1yh004c><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Tea Test&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Jewel-Tea Delivery&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;The fragrance is unique. The bud looks like a hard jewel but it is soft if you touch it.

Could you bring this tea to Coco?  I always wanted her to taste a tea first and tell her to give me a review about it later.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;What about the review?&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;(Coco wrinkles her nose by looking at the tea) This is Amalrie's tea?  If I take this, send rescue signs to Mathew&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ef1yh004c><ef1yh005a><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;A new Information about Monsters&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Auder Hunting&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;We were able to enter Droes in the past, but it has closed for some reasons and the Monsters seem to have changed a lot in the sealed period. We are checking the data of the past with monsters these days, and we discovered many differences between the past and the present after checking the information about Retis, Mr. Hans brought to us. So we are collecting information about new monsters.

Could you do me a favour? Inform me about Auder's datas this time because we already have the information about Retis.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;The monsters became more outrageous than before.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Thank you. In the future I will entrust you more often with some jobs.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ef1yh005a><ef1yh002c><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;A more reeking Stench&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Auder Second Gerneration Hunting&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;Hum, I discovered, there are guys leaving a more reeking stench than Auder's, as I stopped by Droes lately. Let's eliminate these guys. If some monsters have a worse stench than Auder's, I can't imagine how furious this would made Coco.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;Eliminate them and come back to me! Don't get near Coco until the stench is gone.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;You did a good job. Hell, I can't endure this stench too. Come on! Go ahead to wash yourself.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ef1yh002c><ef1yh001d><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Monster Inspection Report&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Craft Hunting&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;Cell Craft Hunting&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;We've got a request for a Monster Inspection Report from the Magistri. I belong to the Magistri, and I am inhabitant of Cherrytown too. I became a member of the Magistri because of the pirates. They make me work hard.

Yes, I know their intention. I think, they aim at the mineral in Droes. I said it before, that's why the mineral producted in Droes had been sold as long it was open in the past. Moreover, Droes is such unique as you can't find something similar at other places in Florensia and Droes has many rare minerals. Even though I don't know the reason.

It's rather bothersome but special handling is needed for Droes reopening and we  have to collect the monster data. This aim is Craft and Cell Craft. Please do me this favor.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;Damn, I can't leave the Magistri!&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;You're a clean and neat worker as expected. You did a good job.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ef1yh001d><ef1yh006a><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;The Scattered Report(1)&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Frogy Report Collection&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;Something really annoying has happened. We employed an outsider lately because we needed workers. We let him go inspect Frogy, but he was frightened and ran away after Frogy licked him up. And he lost the Frogy report he had taken... The monters really changed very much and each data is of crucial importance.  What a trouble maker he is!  He was fired for neglecting his duties by this reason! Please, return to us the report.  He ran away after meeting Frogy, so the report will come out if you run after Frogy. Ah, add some information if you can. Don't you think you have to do this service for me?&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;Ha ha ha. You are a trustworthy man! Regrettably there can only be one of you.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Did you already come back? Ahha, You've brought some further information. Wait a minute.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ef1yh006a><ef1yh006b><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Scattered Report(2)&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Frogy Report Collection&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;In fact we borrowed this report from chief Briant. So to speak frankly, it is based on data of Cherrytown that the chief has managed. If we 've lost it without any copy, it would be a real bummer. But you brought the report and further information, so the chief won't be angry. Nevertheless I lost my face in front of him. Please take the report to the chief instead of me.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;Next time if we hire outsiders, I'll be more careful. Where are all the talents like you&amp;#x2026;.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Oho, Ms. Coco is so cunning. Give this to me. Tell Coco I am not angry and she doesn't need to worry. hahaha.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ef1yh006b><ef1yh007a><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Regret&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Frogy Leef Hunting&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;You know Frogy living in Droes? They are that sort of monster that used to cause trouble to people passing by Droes. They make a licking and spitting attack with the tongue on the belly. But Frogy actually likes people. In fact their attack is an expression of their favor for us. Unfortunately there is a fatal poison at their saliva. Now no one believes in their favor except for only three people. These three are myself, mathew and you. I explained Frogy's intention to others but all in vain.  You know we also aren't able to educate them. So the only thing we can do is to eliminate them although it's a tough decision. I am afraid I can't do anything else. Please, the number of these guys should be reduced by your hands.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;I've already reduced their number in the past. Now it's your turn.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;You're heart must have suffered a lot. You did a good job&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ef1yh007a><ef1yh007b><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Amalrie's Tea for Fatigue Recovery&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Jewel-Leaf Collection&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;Um&amp;#x2026; You looked so tired as you passed by before. So I thought, I help you a little? Do you have Jewel Grass? The tea boiled with Jewel-Leafs is helpful to reduce weariness. If you bring me some, I'll brew the tea for you. If you want it, you can get it from Cell Craft.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;Don't worry about it. The tests are finished.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Wow. You really brought a lot. Fell free to stop by whenever you feel tired.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ef1yh007b><ef1yh008a><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Report Improvement&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Auder Second Generation Report Collection&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;Ts, an official document came in by the Magistri, that is claiming the missing information about Auder Second Generation. Shit, I omitted it because they didn't exist in the past. So how did they come to know about the Auder Second Generation? Anyway I have to research it, so we can take the chance and do it now, can't we? Go and seek for the information of Auder Second Generation. A great prize is awaiting you.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;I have to report all in one go, haven't I?&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;That's alright. Please help me again next time.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ef1yh008a><ec1ym661a><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Unique Wings&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Collect Thirteen Leaves Wings&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt; Hey, come here!  Are you going to Droes Dungeon? I am about to request something, is that alright?

To cut to the chase, you heard for sure the entrance to Droes Dungeon reopened. See, there are monsters called Auder with a unique look.
They love all comestibles very much. After attracting their attention I came to see a wing like leaves on their back. I didn't know what it was made of, but thought it would be ingenious material to craft defensive weapons. So I was going to steal these wings, and find out what they're made of. But I was attacked badly. In the end I had to run away.

Can you fetch the Leaves Wings instead of me? Because you are going to go there anyway. you don't need to go twice, do you? Please do me a favor~ hehe&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;Be careful! It is said Auder throws some stuff out of its hands. The destructive power of it is quite gigantic. I didn't run away for nothing. Be more careful than careful~&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Wow! You brought me so many. Thank you~ I'll analyze this right away. I have to make you a better price for this really good defensive weapons when they're completed~ But I don't know if i do it&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ec1ym661a><ec1ym651b><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Starting Desire&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Collect Twenty Light flowers&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;Come here. Don't go shopping. I have a request this time. Thank you again for bringing me the Parasitic Stone last time. But I was not perfectly satisfied with the grade of the stuff. So can you bring me some other stuff?

 You have to go quite a bit deeper inside Droes Dungeon. There is a monster made of wood but it looks like a mushroom. It is called Craft. I don't know if it's a flower or not. Let's call it a flower briefly. Anyway bring me  the light object at the end of its head. I don't know if it's dangerous or not, but I trust you. I'll be waiting for you to bring it to me.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt; I don't know whether Craft attacks directly or in the distance, if it's hostile or friendly. For more detailed information, you'll need to inspect it directly.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;So this is the light flower. Looks like a flower and even not&amp;#x2026; Tststs, this will let a lot of curiosity arise. You solved the hard task well this time too. I am really satisfied with the result. Ok, the deal is over. You may as well go now because I am busy.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ec1ym651b><ec1ym651c><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Constant Greed.&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Hunting Twenty Auder Second Generation&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt; I know I need to go into Droes Dungeon this time. I am old and weak but I have to enter this dangerous place, haven't I? It would be best to eliminate monsters in advance so I can walk around. The most important to do is eleminating Auder Second Generation. They can attack in long distance.

So fight carefully and hunt a lot. Avoid the crystals Auder Second Generation throws because they can be dangerous. You better put an eye on it. I will collect them after they fell to the floor. Tsts, so clean up in advance. That way I can pass by safely.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;You didn't go ahead yet?  Please, hurry up. It's urgent.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Ah, you came back. You handled it safely, didn't you?  And&amp;#x2026;You didn't touch the crystals Auder Second Gerneration had, did you? Then I have to go quickly over there.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ec1ym651c><ec1ym661b><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Challenge to a new stuff&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Collect Twenty Light Stem&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;The defensive weapons became better than before. What you brought last time was very good. It had less weight but was hard. The best material for me. Droes Dungeon is quite amazing. New things are discovered every day. And I enjoy the desire of creating something new and the challenge. I have to do it to still my desire. But the preparations for crafting are quite long. So I need your much appreciated help.

 Um... please fetch some material instead of me. Of course I feel guilty to ask for help all the time but I'll request this time, next time and whenever it's needed. But I promise you that I'll reward you very generously. Is this alright?

First of all there are Cell Craft. There is a blue light stuff on their head. It is long and narrow. But....I don't know if it's a stem or a tree. Look at the shiny body. I think it is very good material. Bring me this Light Stem.  And now I have to prepare in advance. Take care of the material.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;According to my memory it'll be at the center or a deeper place of Droes Dungeon. Look for it carefully.  Take your time.~ Where is the hammer you always carry around?&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Oh ho~! As soon as I've finished my preparations, you come around with the material. Do this fit fine with each other? Let me see&amp;#x2026; Hm, this looks pretty good.. My expectations seem not to be wrong. Ah~ My desire to work is overflowing! I have to start now. Don't disturb me, do you get it?
Meanwhile I'll give you the next request. Hold on~&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ec1ym661b><ec1ym671a><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Dabbling Necessity&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Collect Ten Frogy Webby&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt; Hey~! Long time no see! You look good. In fact I summoned you for a request. You've been to Droes Dungeon, haven't you?  Then it is easy to explain. If you go to deeper places of Droes Dungeon, there is a monster called Frogy. It looks like a frog but it is a monster. As expected, something new exist here and there. Speaking to the point, the arms of Frogy are made out of web. I intend to use them privately. But I am not able go there myself because of a request for ship building. So fetch the Frogy Webby instead of me. You don't need to hurry. Take your time. Please do me this favor.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;In fact, Frogy is not an outrageous monster. But we have come to die by their poison. So we have to eliminate them.  I am sorry but it cannot be helped. But don't misunderstand. I didn't ask you out of such a reason.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt; You got it already? I said you may take your time. Anyway thank you for bringing me some without any flaw. Now I go to build the rest of this ship.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ec1ym671a><ec1ym681a><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Material useable in Food, or not.&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Collect Twelve Frogy Leaf&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;How do you do? I have a request today. Have you ever seen Frogy inside Droes Dugeon? You say 'yes'? Then it's easy for me to explain.
If you saw Frogy, you'll come to know there is a unique one among them. They have a Big Leaf on the head and that is called Frogy Leaf. To say it upfront that Big Leaf has many useful effects.

My plan is to use it at teas or food. Frogy is naturally a friendly monster. So you may obtain Frogy Leaf easily. Fplease collect some Frogy Leaf for me&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;If you look for the Big Leaf on the head, you can distinguish them from each other immediately&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Wow~! The leaf is bigger than I thought.  I guess Frogy Leaf is so big in size. Now I'll study how to cook with this material. You look tired. Please rest a while&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ec1ym681a><ec1ym671b><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Making more Sturdy Ships!&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Collect Fifteen Stone Treant Tree&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;Ah~ You're just in time. I was about to contact you. In fact I thought about employing someone else. But I cannot relax except I give the task to you. How far did you go into Droes Dungeon? What can you tell me?
What?! You have gone so far? You must be a man of great ability. Then I don't bother to request. There is monster like a tree at the deeper places of Droes Dungeon. Their name are Stone Treant. Like the name tells, they are trees made of stone. I also didn't know. Isn't it marvelous? The wood extracted of this monster keeps the strength of stones.
I am planning to build a ship with this tree material. I don't know if I can use it as easily as I think. But I have to make sure, haven't I? So what if you bring me Stone Treant Tree and I pay you for that. Really I'd love to use it. Please, help me. Okay?&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;It exists at a quite deep place. Be careful!  Every deep place is dangerous.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;This is Stone Treant Tree. You are really trustworthy. By sending you I have nothing to worry about. So I can wait in peace and everything is going well. Haha. Then let me check how this tree works.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ec1ym671b><ec1ym691a><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Odd Disease.&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Collect Five Lure Stone Treant Spores&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt; More people are entering Droes Dungeon lately. It's not determined but the rumor that someone get many jewels in Droes Dungeon seems to affect the people.
By the way, several inhabitants show an odd symptom. Their bodies become stiff little by little. Fortunately, this disease turns out not to be contagious,  so we don't need to worry about an evacuation or something like that. While we inspected the cause of the disease, we discovered that this inhabitants weren't attacked by monsters and that they felt heavy and odd after seeing Lure Stone Treant.

Lure Stone Treant has a light grass on the head. I am sure it is the cause of all this trouble. But we need a strong evidence. I want to investitage the Spore of Lure Stone Treant. If we inspect the Spore, perhaps we'll get some helpful results.
Before more people fall ill, I request of you to bring me these Spores.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;If you go without completed preparations, you may get the disease. You'll have to prepare good enough.  Please, be careful.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;I hope this turns out to show the right result. We have to finish this inspection quickly before the damage increases.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ec1ym691a><ec1ym692a><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;A Feeling of Strange Air in Droes&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Collect Five Parasitic Stone&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;Collect Five Jewel-Flower&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;Collect Five Frogy Leaf&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt; Hey. Have you gone to Droes Dungeon these days? Ah.. , Didn't you feel something strange as you walked through? I sense something very odd from Droes Dungeon. I cannot concentrat on my work because of this sinister hunch.
But a man have to do what a man have to do. I know I have to go and inspect it directly. But it's not easy to do that. Can you go and inspect Droes Dungeon instead of me? I guess It's not a difficult thing. You have to sollect only several stuffs I want.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;I hope my sinister hunch has no deeper meaning.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt; Thank you. If I check this, everything will become clear. Perhaps I have a request after again. If necessary I want you to keep going. I'll come to know after checking these at first.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ec1ym692a><ec1ym701a><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;The Cause of the Disease&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Hunt Thirty Lure Stone Treant&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;We finished the inspection of Lure Stone Treant Spore. As I expected, this Spore floats in the air and enters the body. Then the body becomes stiff like stone. Because some medicine was prescribed, the sick people are gradually recovering, and sonn will be completely cured. But the Spores are still floating and are goingt to spread sooner or later. We have to prevent this case. Go to Droes Dungeon and eliminate Lure Stone Treant now.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;Be careful not to inhale the floating Spores in the air.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;If we reduce their number to some extent, they should not leave Droes Dungeon. Even if they come out, we don't need to worry about it, because of the small number.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ec1ym701a></diff><new><scrxmas01> scrxmas01</scrxmas01><scrxmas02> scrxmas02</scrxmas02><scrxmas03> scrxmas03</scrxmas03><scrxmas04> scrxmas04</scrxmas04><scrxmas05> scrxmas05</scrxmas05><scrxmas06> scrxmas06</scrxmas06><scrxmas07> scrxmas07</scrxmas07><scrxmas08> scrxmas08</scrxmas08></new><settings><searchkey> questlistid</searchkey><ignore> id</ignore><columnnametable> </columnnametable><parsexml> </parsexml></settings></server_questtext_EN></number61><number62><server_questtext_ESP><diff><bc2gt005a><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
